  "texts": [
    "• CoNLL 2003 (https://huggingface.co/datasets/conll2003): CoNLL-2003 serves as a named entity recognition dataset 73 introduced within the framework of the CoNLL-2003 shared task, focusing on language-independent named entity recognition.",
    "This dataset comprises eight files that encompass two languages: English and German.",
    "We have utilized the English dataset and \"ner tags\" as labels for our experiment.",
    "The publicly available version includes 14,041 examples designated for training along with 3250 for validation examples, while 3453 examples are for testing.",
    "• NCBI Disease (https://huggingface.co/datasets/ncbi_disease): The dataset 74 includes annotations for disease names and concepts from the NCBI disease corpus, which is a compilation of 793 PubMed abstracts extensively annotated at both the mention and concept levels."
  ],
